# car-payment-gateway — Rules (Go + Clean Architecture)

These rules keep changes small, testable, and aligned with the project's dependency boundaries.

## Architecture boundaries (must keep)

- **Domain is pure**: code under `internal/domain/**` must not import HTTP/adapters/providers.
- **Application orchestrates**: code under `internal/application/**` may depend on domain types/services and **ports** (interfaces), never concrete adapters.
- **Adapters translate**: code under `internal/adapters/**` handles I/O, parsing, status codes, provider wire formats; it must not embed business rules.
- **Composition only in `cmd/api`**: wiring, env parsing, timeouts, graceful shutdown, route registration.

## Live coding / AI workflow (how to work professionally)

When asked to implement a change:

- **Say the plan first**: what files you’ll touch and why (1 sentence).
- **Change in small commits**: one behavior change at a time (no drive-by refactors).
- **Tests first when possible**:
  - Domain rule → unit test in `internal/domain/**`.
  - Fallback/orchestration → unit test in `internal/application/usecase/**`.
  - HTTP contract → handler test in `internal/adapters/httpapi/**`.
- **Run the suite**: `make test` (use `make test-race` if concurrency is involved).
- **Keep logs safe**: never log full plates; always use `pkg/logger.MaskPlate`.

## Error handling & contracts

- HTTP handler must keep strict input handling:
  - `MaxBytesReader` (1 MiB), `DisallowUnknownFields`, validate `placa`.
  - Map known errors: unknown debt types → 400, all providers failed → 503.
- Do not return provider-specific errors to clients; keep internal details in logs only.

## Money & rounding

- Monetary values must use `github.com/shopspring/decimal`.
- Round only at boundaries (API output / totals) and keep behavior deterministic.
- Never introduce `float64` for currency.

## Provider behavior (resilience)

- Per-provider timeouts must remain (see `providerTimeout` in `ConsultDebts`).
- Preserve “first success wins” fallback semantics.
- If adding a new provider, implement the `provider.Provider` port and register it in `cmd/api/main.go`.

## Examples (what “good” looks like)

### Add a new debt type

- Add constant in `internal/domain/entity`.
- Add an `InterestStrategy` in `internal/domain/service/interest.go`.
- Add a unit test in `internal/domain/service/interest_test.go`.

### Add HTTP middleware

- Implement in `internal/adapters/httpapi/middleware.go`.
- Wire in `cmd/api/main.go`.
- Add/adjust handler tests for status codes and headers.

